The [Curtiss-Wright](/Curtiss-Wright) AT-9 Jeep: an American [World War II](/World_War_II) twin-engine advanced trainer aircraft. Or, as some might prefer, a rather blunt instrument designed to filter out the faint of heart from the fledgling pilots destined for multi-engine combat.

"CW-25" redirects here. For the CW affiliate in South Bend, Indiana, see [WCWW-LD](/WCWW-LD).

